Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{250} and then cut it into slices (3 per person). Place them into a #small bowl{} with cold water and leave to soak. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. In a small bowl, combine the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the pepper and fry, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a plate lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry. Once the pan is hot, add the halloumi and @Cajun blackening{1%capsule}. Stir to coat, then fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Whilst the halloumi fries, pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into a #bowl{} and mix together to make your dressing. Add the @wild rocket{20%g} and toss to coat. Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and place on the middle shelf of your oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once golden, remove the halloumi from the frying pan and cut each slice in half. Pop the warmed tortillas (3 per person) onto your #plates{} and spread a spoonful of sweet chilli mayo over each. Top with the rocket salad, cooked peppers and halloumi fingers (2 per wrap). Serve with the wedges alongside. Enjoy!